## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [CS9868]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;seed is wrinkled to a variable degree; the underlying defect is aberrant cell division within the endosperm and, to a lesser extent, within the embryo 
   - [SALK_048191]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Embryonic lethal in homozygotes.
   - [ede1-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Mutants display 66% seed abortion, with both brown shrunken seeds (late abortion) and small white desiccated seeds (early abortion).  Cellularization of endosperm is not observed.  Microtubule organization in endosperm in defective.
